commit.message: Restore version to latest published one, 1.2.1.
Remove RegexpFactory, which is moved to the Regexpress gem.
Add create method to regexp factory.
Create RegexpFactory.
Update to use current gem layout and configuration.
Refine rcfile tests.
Add local glark config, to skip pkg directory
Remove unused variable
Change File#exists to File#exist

Fixed warning from Regexp about patterns not matching word boundaries.

With an misleading Regexp pattern, resulting in '\b:foo\b/', the warning was
attempted to be written to the obsolete Log. This fix raises an exception
instead.
Code/whitespace cleanup.
Expanded Enumerable tests. Moved into RIEL module.
Cleaned up tests and formatting.
Updated features.
Began to move optproc into its own module.
Removed dependency on RIEL::String.
Moved extensions to core Ruby classes to RIEL modules.
Removed riel/log code; migrated to logue.
Added require of pathname.
Added format class for log.
v1.1.18 -- fixed for 1.9 warnings. Added require for Enumerable change to detect/select.
Removed unused requires.
asciitable: moved to a separate gem.
Moved color palette code to pirahue.
log: fully changed dependency to Rainbow.
log: reduced number of methods.
log: added tests.
log: added format tests.
log: fixed for changes between 1.8 and 1.9.
